This page is a supplementary teaching scaffold for target planning and backend lowering.

## Core concept

A backend should receive explicit validated semantic inputs. It should not reconstruct source meaning while generating target code.

## Beanstalk boundary

The build system owns:

- entry and package roots
- reachability unions
- target assignment
- project assembly
- output records and manifests

The compiler owns target-contract validation over explicit roots and assignments.

Lowerers own target-specific code generation from validated HIR, type environments, borrow facts and link plans.

Unsupported reachable features are diagnosed before lowering. Lowerers do not parse source, rebuild imports, infer generics or write final project outputs directly.

## Rewrite focus

Explain the distinction between target validation, link planning, code generation and output writing.

Canonical details live in both architecture authorities.
